comments.body:
Responding to https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/30377/files#r1716693711:
@maflcko: Might introduce `VecFromHex` for tests but I like that this constant is fully compile time.

@paplorinc: I have been trying out exactly that approach quite a bit, but was [warned by maflcko](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/30377#discussion_r1692989490) that there may be lying dragons among the different serializations of `vector`/`array`/`span`/`Span`. Also had some annoying MSVC compiler errors when just trying to add an overload for `std::array`. So undid my changes to that class.

