comments.body:
That's strange, I don't see how a string literal would need a conversion when there's a `const char*` ctor? It seems to work fine for [`ConstevalStringLiteral`](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/2f7d9aec4d049701fccfc029f44934d187467432/src/util/translation.h#L72) too, so pardon my insistence but I think perhaps this compiler error might be because of another issue? Would you mind trying this diff on 734ac5a9002493013c0f8afe763f751ac99f89c8?

<details>
<summary>git diff on 734ac5a900</summary>

```diff
diff --git a/src/util/strencodings.h b/src/util/strencodings.h
index fbd116c77c..63f46396d3 100644
--- a/src/util/strencodings.h
+++ b/src/util/strencodings.h
@@ -80,8 +80,7 @@ consteval uint8_t ConstevalHexDigit(const char c)
 
 struct ConstevalHexLiteral {
     const std::string_view inner;
-    template <size_t N>
-    consteval ConstevalHexLiteral(const char (&hex_str)[N]) : ConstevalHexLiteral{std::string_view{hex_str}} {}
+    consteval ConstevalHexLiteral(const char* hex_str) : ConstevalHexLiteral{std::string_view{hex_str}} {}
     consteval ConstevalHexLiteral(const std::string_view hex_str) : inner{hex_str} { Validate(inner); }
     consteval ConstevalHexLiteral(std::nullptr_t) = delete;
 

```
</details>

